<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Lesson: Economic Geography Master Module</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Crimson+Pro:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Inter:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/lucide@latest"></script>
    <style>
        body { font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif; background: #fdfbf7; line-height: 1.7; }
        .page { background: white; max-width: 900px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 60px 80px; box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); border-radius: 32px; border: 1px solid #f1f5f9; }
        .action { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 24px; color: #1e293b; font-size: 0.95rem; }
        .dialogue { margin-left: 40px; font-style: italic; color: #475569; position: relative; margin-bottom: 12px; }
        .dialogue::before { content: "—"; position: absolute; left: -20px; color: #cbd5e1; font-style: normal; }
        .material-box { background: #f8fafc; border-radius: 20px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; padding: 30px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
        .aside-box { background: #fffbeb; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; padding: 25px; margin: 40px 0; border-radius: 0 15px 15px 0; position: relative; }
        .aside-box::after { content: "Instructor's Aside"; position: absolute; top: -10px; left: 20px; background: #f59e0b; color: white; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 8px; font-weight: 900; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; }
        .illustrate { border: 2px dashed #e2e8f0; border-radius: 20px; margin: 35px 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: #fcfcfc; padding: 30px; }
        .illustrate-label { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; color: #94a3b8; margin-top: 15px; }
        @media print { body { background: white; margin: 0; } .page { box-shadow: none; border: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; width: 100%; } .no-print { display: none; } }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="no-print p-6 flex justify-between items-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <a href="../../index.html" class="text-slate-400 font-bold uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2">
            <i data-lucide="arrow-left" size="14"></i> Back to Dashboard
        </a>
        <button onclick="window.print()" class="bg-amber-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded-full font-bold shadow-lg hover:bg-amber-700 transition-all flex items-center gap-2">
            <i data-lucide="printer" size="16"></i> Print to PDF
        </button>
    </div>
    
    <article class="page">
        <header class="mb-12 border-b-2 border-amber-50 pb-8">
            <p class="font-sans font-bold text-amber-600 uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-2 italic">Geography // Human Interdependencies</p>
            <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 leading-tight">Economic Geography Master Module</h1>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400 italic">Guide: Elim Lee // AMI Elementary Submission</p>
        </header>

        <!-- MATERIAL BOX -->
        <section class="material-box">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-bold text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-4">Direct Aim</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 italic mb-6">To explore how humans transform natural resources into products, and how these are distributed and consumed across the world.</p>
            <h3 class="font-sans font-bold text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-2">Materials</h3>
            <p class="text-[11px] leading-relaxed text-slate-600 font-sans uppercase font-bold tracking-wider">Outline maps (State, National, World), resource stamps/symbols, colored pencils, graph paper, rulers (mm), and atlases/almanacs.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- PRESENTATION I -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-amber-600 mb-8 border-b pb-2 italic">Part I: Local Production (The Unit)</h2>
            <div class="action">Invite the child and review their recent research on local resources (e.g., Ranches).</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"You found all these different ranches in Arizona. I wonder what that would look like on a map? Let's use this cow stamp. One stamp will represent one ranch."</div>
            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="300" height="200" viewBox="0 0 300 200" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <path d="M100 20 L200 20 L210 150 L90 150 L90 80 Z" stroke="#CBD5E1" stroke-width="2" fill="#F8FAFC"/>
                    <circle cx="150" cy="60" r="6" fill="#B45309" opacity="0.6"/>
                    <circle cx="140" cy="80" r="6" fill="#B45309" opacity="0.6"/>
                    <rect x="220" y="100" width="60" height="40" rx="4" stroke="#94A3B8" fill="white"/>
                    <text x="225" y="115" font-family="Inter" font-size="6" font-weight="bold">KEY</text>
                    <circle cx="230" cy="125" r="3" fill="#B45309"/>
                    <text x="238" y="128" font-family="Inter" font-size="6">= 1 Ranch</text>
                </svg>
                <div class="illustrate-label">Fig 1.1: Mapping Local Production via Units</div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- PRESENTATION II -->
        <section class="mt-16">
            <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-amber-600 mb-8 border-b pb-2 italic">Part II: Perspective (Percentage vs. Quantity)</h2>
            <div class="action">Introduce a national map. Show Arizona with only a "half-cow" symbol.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"Wait! On our other map, Arizona had many stamps. Why is there only half a cow here? Ah, look at the legend: '1 Cow = 1% of USA Beef.' This map tells a different story—not how many ranches, but how much of the whole country's beef comes from here."</div>
            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="400" height="120" viewBox="0 0 400 120" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <rect x="50" y="20" width="300" height="80" rx="8" fill="#F1F5F9" stroke="#94A3B8"/>
                    <path d="M80 50 Q90 40 100 50 L100 70 Q90 80 80 70 Z" fill="#B45309" opacity="0.4"/> <!-- Half cow sketch -->
                    <text x="110" y="65" font-family="Inter" font-size="10" fill="#64748B">ARIZONA (0.5%)</text>
                </svg>
                <div class="illustrate-label">Fig 2.1: The shift from local count to national ratio</div>
            </section>

        <!-- PRESENTATION III -->
        <section class="mt-16">
            <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-amber-600 mb-8 border-b pb-2 italic">Part III: Consumption (Conversion & Logic)</h2>
            <div class="action">Start a conversation about daily habits (e.g., Milk).</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"If one person drinks one quart of milk a day, how much do they drink in a year? Ninety gallons! Now, if there are 332 million people in the U.S., how much milk do we consume altogether?"</div>
            <div class="action">Help children organize a table or graph (Compatible Numbers).</div>
            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="400" height="150" viewBox="0 0 400 150" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <!-- Bar graph sketch -->
                    <line x1="40" y1="20" x2="40" y2="120" stroke="#94A3B8"/>
                    <line x1="40" y1="120" x2="300" y2="120" stroke="#94A3B8"/>
                    <rect x="60" y="40" width="40" height="80" fill="#3B82F6" opacity="0.6"/>
                    <rect x="120" y="60" width="40" height="60" fill="#F59E0B" opacity="0.6"/>
                    <text x="50" y="135" font-family="Inter" font-size="8" fill="#64748B">STATE A</text>
                    <text x="110" y="135" font-family="Inter" font-size="8" fill="#64748B">STATE B</text>
                </svg>
                <div class="illustrate-label">Fig 3.1: Comparative Consumption Graph (Eggs/Milk)</div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- PRESENTATION IV -->
        <section class="mt-16">
            <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-amber-600 mb-8 border-b pb-2 italic">Part IV: Volume and Trade (Global Network)</h2>
            <div class="action">Introduce a world map. Use a ruler with millimeters.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"We are going to be precise with our volume today. The thickness of the line between countries will show how much they trade. 1mm will equal 20 Billion dollars."</div>
            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="400" height="150" viewBox="0 0 400 150" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <!-- Line thickness demo -->
                    <line x1="50" y1="40" x2="200" y2="40" stroke="#1D4ED8" stroke-width="8"/> <!-- Major Trade -->
                    <text x="210" y="45" font-family="Inter" font-size="8" fill="#1e293b">CHINA (Heavy Trade)</text>
                    <line x1="50" y1="80" x2="200" y2="80" stroke="#1D4ED8" stroke-width="1"/> <!-- Minor Trade -->
                    <text x="210" y="85" font-family="Inter" font-size="8" fill="#1e293b">IRELAND (Light Trade)</text>
                </svg>
                <div class="illustrate-label">Fig 4.1: Volume of Trade represented by Line Weight</div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <div class="aside-box text-sm italic text-amber-900 leading-relaxed">
            "Avoid moving to the computer immediately for research. Let children discover information through physical resource books (almanacs, atlases) first to build their inquiry skills. Also, prepare an 'ink station' in the classroom to prevent the stamps from becoming a barrier to work."
        </div>

        <footer class="mt-20 pt-8 border-t text-[10px] font-sans text-slate-300 uppercase tracking-widest text-center">
            Elim Lee // Semester 3 Catch-Up // AMI Elementary
        </footer>
    </article>
    <script>lucide.createIcons();</script>
</body>
</html>
